Neural Networks, Probabilistic Methods. 

Neural Networks: The paper uses a single neural network for the second model to predict the residual error of the first model. 

Probabilistic Methods: The first model is a mixture of experts that predicts the electricity demand from exogenous variables and can be viewed as a nonlinear regression model of mixture of Gaussians. The paper also analyzes the splitting of the input space generated by the mixture of experts model, which is a probabilistic method.
